#compdef readur
# =============================================================================
# readur — Readur org's "Quick, painless, intuitive
#          OCR platform written in Rust and TypeScript.
#          Modern UI with modern API, with an emphasis
#          on intuitive user experience" — a self-
#          hostable document-management server with
#          built-in optical character recognition
#          (OCR), full-text search, WebDAV browsing,
#          tagged folders, and a modern React-based
#          web UI.  The Rust backend serves the API
#          + handles OCR processing via Tesseract +
#          stores extracted text + metadata in
#          PostgreSQL or SQLite via SQLx.
#          Distinguishing from Paperless-ngx (Python
#          + Django; the dominant self-hosted document
#          management option), DocumentServer-NG (Java
#          based), Mayan EDMS (Python+Django), and
#          enterprise-level commercial DMS solutions
#          (M-Files, OpenText) by:
#            - OCR-FIRST DESIGN — every uploaded
#              document automatically OCR'd through
#              Tesseract; extracted text indexed for
#              full-text search; users can search
#              "find that invoice from 2023 with
#              $1,500" and find it
#            - WEBDAV BROWSING — built-in WebDAV
#              client to ingest documents from
#              external storage (NAS, Nextcloud,
#              Synology shares); analyzed via the
#              `analyze-webdav-performance` companion
#              binary
#            - UTOIPA OPENAPI — uses Juhana Helovuo's
#              utoipa Rust crate (this is the headline
#              CLI library that opens Axis 38 on the
#              Rust side; see taxonomy notes below)
#              to auto-generate OpenAPI 3.x
#              specifications from Rust source code +
#              utoipa-swagger-ui to serve interactive
#              Swagger UI at /docs
#            - AXUM HTTP — built on tokio-rs/axum
#              (Axis 26 covered) for the API server
#              layer
#            - SQLX DATABASE — uses launchbadge/sqlx
#              (compile-time-checked SQL queries; the
#              non-ORM alternative to diesel R729) for
#              PostgreSQL + SQLite backends
#            - TOWER MIDDLEWARE — tower-http (CORS,
#              static files, compression) + tower
#              core middleware composition
#            - MODERN UI — React + Vite + TypeScript
#              frontend served from `frontend/dist`
#              by Axum's ServeDir
#            - DUAL-DEPLOYMENT — works as a single
#              binary (`readur serve`) for development
#              or as a Docker compose stack
#              (Dockerfile + Dockerfile.dev +
#              Dockerfile.stress)
#            - RESET-ADMIN-PASSWORD UTILITY — `readur
#              reset-admin-password` is the
#              emergency-recovery command for
#              regaining admin access if password is
#              lost
#            - TEST RUNNER + WEBDAV ANALYZER — bundled
#              companion binaries:
#              * `test_runner` — runs the integrated
#                test suite
#              * `analyze-webdav-performance` —
#                profiles WebDAV ingestion against
#                external storage
#            - 742+ STARS — production-suitable self-
#              hosted alternative to commercial DMS
#              + the established Python-based open-
#              source options
#          Used by: self-hosting enthusiasts replacing
#          Paperless-ngx with a Rust-based alternative,
#          small businesses wanting OCR + full-text
#          search over their document archives, legal
#          + healthcare offices needing on-premises
#          document management without cloud
#          dependence, and individual professionals
#          digitizing paper archives.
#
